cff-version: 1.2.0
title: "ITU and Law & Jurisprudence: A Single-Axiom View of Constitutional Law, Criminal Law, Civil Law, International Law, Human Rights, AI Ethics, Intellectual Property, and Procedural Justice — Pass-1 Extension Paper #5, Block C 3/6"
message: "If you use this work, please cite it as below."
type: software
authors:
  - family-names: Terada
    given-names: Munehiro
    affiliation: Roboken
    email: munehiro.terada@roboken2.com
abstract: >
  We apply the Information-Theoretic Unification (ITU) framework
  (Terada 2026, concept DOI 10.5281/zenodo.20109209; Tier 0 v3.0 at
  10.5281/zenodo.20200156) to law and jurisprudence. Tier 1 paper #35,
  the fifth paper of Pass-1 extension, Block C 3/6 (HALF MILESTONE of
  social/humanities/arts). Introduces K_law across 8 sub-states
  (constitutional, criminal, civil, international, human rights,
  AI ethics, IP, procedural). ITU axiom delta S = delta <K> verified
  to machine precision in 11 contexts. 35-vertex ITU polytope.
  Theoretical position: Law operates as K-state normalization
  mechanism; constitutional law = top prior; criminal/civil law =
  norm-violation + private agreement regulation; international law =
  national K-state coordination; AI ethics = new K-state attractor
  for digital age.
  Key results: Hammurabi BC 1754 (282 articles); Roman 12 Tables
  BC 450; Justinian Corpus Iuris Civilis AD 533; Magna Carta 1215;
  Grotius De Jure Belli ac Pacis 1625; Beccaria Dei delitti e delle
  pene 1764 (deterrence: certainty > celerity > severity);
  Montesquieu De l'Esprit des Lois 1748 (separation of powers);
  US Constitution 1787 + Bill of Rights 1791; Napoleon Code Civil
  1804 (2,281 articles, influence 30+ countries); French Declaration
  of Rights 1789 (Liberte, Egalite, Fraternite); BGB 1900 (Germany,
  2,385 articles); Japan Civil Code 1898; Marbury v. Madison 1803
  (judicial review); Brown v. Board 1954; Roe v. Wade 1973 -> Dobbs
  2022 overturn; Japan Supreme Court 11 unconstitutional rulings in
  77 years; Miranda v. Arizona 1966; Habeas Corpus Act 1679;
  Donoghue v. Stevenson 1932 UK; Roundup litigation $11B+ settlement;
  Coase theorem 1960 (Nobel Economics 1991); Becker 1968 crime
  economics (Nobel 1992).
  International: UN Charter 1945 (193 members 2024); UNSC P5 vetoes
  1946-2024 (Russia/USSR 156, US 89, UK 32, China 23, France 18);
  WTO 1995 (164 members); Paris Agreement 2015.12.12 (196 parties);
  COP29 Baku 2024 $300B/yr climate finance; UNCLOS 1982 (EEZ 200 nm);
  Geneva Conventions 1949; ICC Rome Statute 1998 (124 countries);
  Lubanga 2012 first ICC verdict; Putin arrest warrant 2023.3;
  Netanyahu + Gallant arrest warrants 2024.5.
  Human rights: UDHR 1948.12.10 (30 articles, Rene Cassin Nobel
  Peace 1968 for drafting); ICCPR + ICESCR 1966; CEDAW 1979
  (189 countries); CAT 1984 (173 countries); ECHR 1950 + ECtHR 1959
  (Russia expelled 2022.3); same-sex marriage 36 countries (2024);
  Nadia Murad + Denis Mukwege Nobel Peace 2018; Narges Mohammadi
  Nobel Peace 2023; WEF Gender Gap Japan rank 118/146 (2024);
  #MeToo 2017.10; death penalty 112 abolitionist vs 53 retentionist
  (Amnesty 2023).
  Tech law: EU AI Act 2024.3.13/8.1 (max EUR35M or 7% global
  turnover, risk tiers Unacceptable/High/Limited/Minimal); Biden EO
  14110 2023.10.30 -> Trump revocation 2025; Colorado AI Act 2024;
  CA SB 1047 2024 vetoed; China generative AI rules 2023.8.15; G7
  Hiroshima AI Process 2023.5; Berne Convention 1886 (life + 70 yr);
  PCT 1970 (157 countries); TRIPS 1995 (20-year patent); China
  patents 1.7M (>50% world, 2024); Apple v. Samsung $539M; NY Times
  v. OpenAI 2023.12; Getty Images v. Stability AI $1.8B 2023;
  Suno + Udio v. RIAA $150K/song 2024; US Copyright Office 2023
  "AI-generated NOT copyrightable"; Andy Warhol Foundation v.
  Goldsmith 2023 Supreme Court (transformative use restricted);
  GDPR 2018.5.25 (Meta EUR1.2B fine 2023, Amazon EUR746M 2021);
  CCPA, LGPD, PIPL, APPI updates; Budapest Convention 2001
  (68 countries); Tesla Autopilot 46 deaths NHTSA 2024.
  Ten falsifiable predictions (P_avg = 0.810 — Pass-1+extension
  second-highest after #34's 0.825; Strong/Medium/Weak = 9/1/0
  tied for HIGHEST) including EU AI Act full enforcement 2027
  (P=0.85, Strong), AI Fair Use US verdict 2026 (P=0.85, Strong),
  AI Liability Directive EU 2026 (P=0.85, Strong), AI international
  treaty G7/G20 2027 (P=0.80, Strong), same-sex marriage 50+
  countries 2030 (P=0.80, Strong), AI contract review 50% standard
  2028 (P=0.85, Strong), DNA exoneration 1,000+ US 2030 (P=0.85,
  Strong), AI sentencing 50% 2028 (P=0.80, Strong), face recognition
  regulation 30+ countries 2027 (P=0.85, Strong), WIPO international
  IP unified 2030 (P=0.60, Medium). Block C HALF MILESTONE 3/6 = 50%.
  Pass-1 interpretive synthesis.
